then we will go to the web browser and run our code

22
00:01:46.580 --> 00:01:50.800
noticed that currently the table has its border separate from the cell borders.

23
00:01:50.810 --> 00:01:59.570
Let's jump back to the editor as we noted the table had its own border separate from the cell borders.

24
00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:05.440
If this is not desirable we can use the border collapse property and give it a value of collapse.

25
00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:08.510
We will assign this property to the table element.

26
00:02:08.510 --> 00:02:13.820
Then we will go to the web browser and run our code.

27
00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:18.290
Now you will notice that the table and cell borders are collapsed into one border.

28
00:02:18.290 --> 00:02:21.990
Let's jump back to the editor.

29
00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:27.120
We can give our table a width and height as pixel values or as percentages using the width and height

30
00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:28.320
properties.

31
00:02:28.320 --> 00:02:32.950
Let's give our table a width and height of 100 percent.

32
00:02:33.210 --> 00:02:38.270
Then we will go to the web browser and run our code.

33
00:02:38.300 --> 00:02:42.610
Let's jump back to the editor.

34
00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:45.930
We can add a caption to our table using the caption tag.

35
00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:53.710
Let's add an opening and closing caption tag and give our table a caption to see the caption we just

36
00:02:53.710 --> 00:02:54.750
add it to the table.

37
00:02:54.760 --> 00:03:02.830
Let's go to the web browser and write our code as you can see the caption is displayed above the table.

38
00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:04.450
Let's jump back to the editor.

39
00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:12.260
CSSA gives us the caption side property which allows us to specify where to place the table caption

40
00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:16.420
of value of top we'll put the caption at the top of the table.

41
00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:21.910
Let's go to our style code and give our caption a caption side property with a value of top.

42
00:03:21.980 --> 00:03:24.220
Then we will go to the web browser and run our code

43
00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.940
as you can see the captions at the top of our table.

44
00:03:29.940 --> 00:03:35.720
The caption hasn't moved since the last example since Top is the default value of the caption side property.

45
00:03:35.880 --> 00:03:38.750
Let's jump back to the editor and look at another example.

46
00:03:41.570 --> 00:03:47.270
Assigning the caption side property a value of bottom will put the caption at the bottom of our table.

